Writing a code for tree:
 
1. Main function, taking just the node and calling another function that takes the node and the reference values (isBST in this case)
2. second function will first have null check, and return as the base case. 
3. followed by verifying the condition, (the if part here), this might have recursive calls
4. Compute information required for the node above, and set to the reference variables provided, and return
 
Template:
 
main_function(node)  // Step 1
{
   working_function(node, reference1, reference2, ...)
}
 
working_function(node, reference1, reference2, … ) {
    if(node == NULL) {blah blah blah return;}  // step 2
    if (recursive calls , and condition check) // step 3
    {
        set reference1, set reference2, …. // step 4
       return
    }
   else {
       // almost same as if  // step 4
    }
}
 
